The paper deals with decentralized estimation, which involves communication constraints and information processing. This suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of strong data processing inequalities and the treatment of multiple processors suggest that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The consideration of quantization and noise in communication channels suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the discussion of interactive communication protocols suggests that it may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category.
